## Steps

### step 1
id: navigate-to-scrub-rules
instruction: Click "Scrub Rules" in the main sidebar under "Altair Intelligence."
success_criteria: You are on the Scrub Rules page showing two tabs: CMS Rules and Custom Rules. Each tab shows a rule count.
anchor: "Scrub Rules"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The link is in the sidebar under "Altair Intelligence."

### step 2
id: explore-cms-rules
instruction: Click the "CMS Rules" tab. These are standard Medicare/Medicaid billing rules pre-configured by Altair — code pairs, modifier requirements, gender/age restrictions, and more. Each rule has a toggle to enable or disable it.
success_criteria: You can see CMS Rules listed by category with descriptions and enable/disable toggles.
anchor: "CMS Rules"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Click the CMS Rules tab at the top of the page.

### step 3
id: explore-custom-rules
instruction: Click the "Custom Rules" tab. These are rules specific to your practice — either created by your team or proposed by Altair based on denial patterns.
success_criteria: You can see custom rules listed, and any "Proposed Rules" (yellow) at the top waiting for your review.
anchor: "Custom Rules"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Click the Custom Rules tab at the top of the page.

### step 4
id: review-proposed-rules
instruction: If you see proposed rules (highlighted in yellow), read their descriptions to understand what Altair is suggesting. You can activate or reject each proposal.
success_criteria: You understand what custom and proposed rules are in place, and which payers they apply to.
anchor: "proposed rule"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Proposed rules appear at the top of the Custom Rules list with a distinct visual treatment.

## Completion Message
you now understand what scrub rules are catching your claims before they go to payers. CMS rules handle federal requirements, custom rules capture your payer-specific patterns. want me to walk you through reviewing and activating a proposed rule?

